Kaduna has recorded two fresh deaths from COVID-19. It brings the fatalities from COVID-19 in the state to three. Governor Nasir el-Rufai identified the latest deceased as a senior citizen from Makarfi and a lady from Zaria. In a tweet on his official Twitter handle, the Governor also informed two more persons have tested positive. The new infections bring the active COVID-19 cases in the state to 87. The two new cases, he said, are a male from Igabi and a female from Chikun local government areas. Kaduna State has 87 active Covid-19 cases and three fatalities. Kaduna recorded its first fatality on May 2.